The paper discusses the use of recurrent neural networks to model reinforcement learning environments and train policies through evolution. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of recurrent neural networks also suggests the possibility of neural evolution (cs.NE). The paper also mentions the use of policies in robotics (cs.RO) and the extraction of spatio-temporal features (cs.CV).
